=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides information about alerts and warnings that Amazon Lex sends
during a migration. The alerts include information about how to resolve
the issue.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Details => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

Additional details about the alert.


=head2 Message => Str

A message that describes why the alert was issued.


=head2 ReferenceURLs => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

A link to the Amazon Lex documentation that describes how to resolve
the alert.


=head2 Type => Str

The type of alert. There are two kinds of alerts:

=over

=item *

C<ERROR> - There was an issue with the migration that can't be
resolved. The migration stops.

=item *

C<WARN> - There was an issue with the migration that requires manual
changes to the new Amazon Lex V2 bot. The migration continues.

=back




